Cool Refuge London


&lt;p class="eyebrow"&gt;CASA0025 Group Application&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Where should London prioritise cooling interventions?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p class="lead"&gt;London’s heat risk is not only a question of high temperature. It is shaped by vegetation, built-surface intensity, population exposure and access to places where people can cool down. This project brings these layers together into an interactive planning-support tool for exploring local cooling conditions across London.&lt;/p&gt;
